  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Danish Hernia Database (DHD) registers 37 different perioperative parameters. The aim of
      present study is to use large-scale data from DHD to uncover risk factors for long-term (30
      days postoperative and later) readmission, reoperation, death and reoperation for recurrence
      after incisional hernia repair with use of a synthetic mesh.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All principal incisional hernias registered in the Danish Hernia Database are included in the
      study. The included patients have been followed for more than 4 years in order to identify
      correlation between technical aspects of the hernia repair and postoperative morbidity.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
